description: From Latin vīvificātus, past participle vīvificō. See vivify.

verbs.description: vivificate (third-person singular simple present vivificates, present participle vivificating, simple past and past participle vivificated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To give life to; to animate.
examples: God vivificates and actuates the whole world.

entries.meaning: (chemistry, obsolete, transitive) To bring back a metal to the metallic form, as from oxide or solution; to reduce.
